snippet.textDisplay:
Ummm... nope. Way too expensive. Insane pricing for a computer monitor. $1500 on an LG will get you all you need and more, and look just as good. Apple has been trying to push the high end for the past few years. Have at it. These prices are for people who want Apple because it's Apple. Even if you are a professional video editor, I've cut enough TV over 30 years to qualify, this monitor isn't good enough to grade on. Equipment is not supposed to be the reason to buy something, profit (how much I can make from these tools) should be the motivating factor. You cannot economically justify this monitor over another. You can't. Target demographic: People who have money to waste on crap (OK it's nice and all...) they don't need.

And NOBODY who is still in business has millions of dollars to "pour" into production. That era ended 20 years ago.

If it's a business decision to put 2 x $6000 dollar monitors on your desk, you are the worst business person I've ever seen.
